Contributions and criticism welcome.

Goto http://www.pyglet.org/download.html

And download the pyglet.   

"sudo python setup.py install" to install.

Pygame is necessary.   Install this:

sudo apt-get install python-pygame

For more information:

http://askubuntu.com/questions/203630/easy-install-pygame-not-working-due-to-linux-videodev-h-no-such-file-or-direct

mv /usr/include/linux/videodev.h /tmp
sudo apt-get install libv4l-dev
cd /usr/include/linux
sudo ln -s ../libv4l1-videodev.h videodev.h

And this:

sudo apt-get install python-dev libsdl-image1.2-dev libsdl-mixer1.2-dev libsdl-ttf2.0-dev   libsdl1.2-dev libsmpeg-dev python-numpy subversion libportmidi-dev ffmpeg libswscale-dev libavformat-dev libavcodec-dev


sudo yum install python-devel SDL_image-devel SDL_mixer-devel SDL_ttf-devel SDL-devel smpeg-devel numpy subversion portmidi-devel 

sudo yum install zlib
yum -y install mingw32-gcc mingw32-SDL mingw32-zlib
sudo yum -y install mingw32-gcc mingw32-SDL mingw32-zlib
yum groupinfo "C Development Tools and Libraries"
sudo yum groups install  "C Development Tools and Libraries"
sudo yum groups install  "Development Tools"
sudo yum install cmake
sudo yum install wget
sudo yum localinstall rpmfusion-free-release-20.noarch.rpm 
sudo yum install rpmfusion-nonfree-release-20.noarch.rpm 
sudo yum install ffmpeg
vi yum.list 
grep -i freetype yum.list 
sudo yum install freetype
vi yum.list 
sudo yum localinstall google-chrome-stable_current_x86_64.rpm 
sudo yum install openssh-server
